task.summary: Yeah... updated code... don't remember what code I updated. :P
SettingsManager and related classes now moved to API with event system to notify interested classes of updates.
Module list implemented - internal Module model changed
Updating implemented with bug (ModType changing to Regular)
Fixed updating, removed extra messages from downloads, added dynamic pack update detection.
Derp... Add default pack to the list on launch.
Add PackBuilder to MCUpdater IDEA workspace
Add PackBuilder to MCUpdater IDEA workspace
Add Main-Class to manifest for MCU-Bootstrap
FastPack! A CLI pack builder for MCU3!
FastPack! A CLI pack builder for MCU3!
Add license files to all projects missing license files.
FastPack now tries to intelligently assign config files to the relevant mods. Not perfect.
Better Mod/Config matching Strip version numbers from non-mcmod.info based mod ids.
Even better Mod/Config matching ModId override list

MCUpdater 3.2.3 - New buttons on instance list to add a new XML and to refresh the list - New setting to toggle Minecraft process output to Console tab (default True) - Properly do settings refreshes with all lists - Added "hard update" checkbox to restore that functionality
Versioning updates Basic HTTP Authentication implemented
Update Version classes to handle launch from IDE.
3.2.6 - Reimplement Program Wrapper and use javaw.exe for Windows.
Import old Swing classes for reuse.
Progress: Browsers should be coded to work properly.
Bumped MCU-DownloadLib to 1.4 due to changes.
Legacy launcher implemented Cache purging implemented
Check for pack updates before launch
Added warning to log when fallback to basic browser implementation occurs
Added test class PackList (outputs CSV of a URL and server id passed as command line args)
I think I've got it coded for getting maven-style library overrides from server packs...
